item.title: Help Proxy-ing
item.dc:creator: @vbcoderx vbcoderx
item.description:
@vbcoderx wrote:

ok i looked at one of the links above and it had the code for the proxyrunbot.bat code but it didn’t have a working proxy i used the wisdom god and found a link to a proxy list and i changed around the code a bit so it works http://www.atomintersoft.com/products/alive-proxy/socks5-list/ that is the site scroll down to the socks5 proxy list and it works @echo off title Running Bot java -DsocksProxyHost=[u]24.7.240.34[u] -DsocksProxyPort=[u]46937[u] -noverify -Xmx500m -cp .;./OUTPUT;./OUTPUT/unrenamed.jar;./BotClasses; Bot pause the parts with the [u] around them are what you would change like that is a usa proxy and it works for me here is a france proxy

@echo off title Running Bot java -DsocksProxyHost=82.232.97.239 -DsocksProxyPort=1080 -noverify -Xmx500m -cp .;./OUTPUT;./OUTPUT/unrenamed.jar;./BotClasses; Bot pause u can copy that if u want if u want to use the USA proxy use this code btw all these need to be in the same folder as your runbot.bat and they all need to be .bat files

@echo off title Running Bot java -DsocksProxyHost=24.7.240.34 -DsocksProxyPort=46937 -noverify -Xmx500m -cp .;./OUTPUT;./OUTPUT/unrenamed.jar;./BotClasses; Bot pause thats the USA proxy wilout the [u]'s in it
here is another proxy list sitehttp://www.samair.ru/proxy/socks5.htm also be sure to check your proxy is working!!! log in when u start aryan with a oroxy then log out then back in and check the ip where u last logged in if it has changed then your proxy has worked u may need to repeat this logout and back in if u have logged in on a different computer before u played on your account on the computer your on

item.title: Help Proxy-ing
item.dc:creator: @zacharymata zacharymata
item.description:
@zacharymata wrote:

Make a new Text document. Edit it . Fill in @echo off title Running Bot java -DsocksProxyHost=69.243.225.60 -DsocksProxyPort=80 -noverify -Xmx500m -cp .;./OUTPUT;./OUTPUT/unrenamed.jar;./BotClasses;./LIB; Bot %1 pause <-- i know the code tags are prob wrong. Fill in the DsocksProxyHost with the IP of a proxy And the DsocksProxyPort with the other part … google socks 5 proxy list… An example of what it looks like is 69.243.225.60::80 … Fill the IP part in the Host and the numbers after the colon in the Port. I know this is sort of like out of order… basically how you do it. After you added all that java info in the text document Save as All Document Like Proxybot.bat , All files , ANSI format… Pretty much how it is., Someone may describe it clearer
